{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11437: Vue crashes when function name is similar to imported component",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:27.964901+00:00",
  "text": "Vue crashes when function name is similar to imported component\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.4\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nno link\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nits easy to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport ViewComponent from '/src/components/ViewComponent.vue' // can be empty file with just a div\r\n\r\nasync function viewComponent(index) { // Similar name. but v is small case\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n...\r\n<view-component  /> \r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nit should work\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\ncrash\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
